videos.description:

Sadly, tiger numbers a dwindling in the wild, and the work we do here at Australia Zoo helps conserve these beautiful animals. videos.title: A message from Bindi - Climate Aid World Forum
videos.description:
From Bindi: "Last year here in Australia we experienced a catastrophic fire event throughout the country. Climate change is to blame for the unbelievable devastation to our native bushland with these fires. Scientists estimate that about 3 billion animal lives perished in these fires and our Wildlife Hospital was busier than ever. Climate change threatens life as we know it and every day I see the toll it takes on our natural environment."

videos.title: Robert introduces our magnificent elephants | Australia Zoo Life
videos.description:
Today is an extremely exciting and historic day at AustraliaZoo! We are thrilled to welcome our Sumatran elephants to their new Elephantasia habitat. Guests can experience and fall in love with our gorgeous elephants and learn about our conservation work protecting this critically endangered species. In the past 25 years, over 70% of their wild habitat has been destroyed in Sumatra, leaving less than 2500 Sumatran elephants in existence. They need our support and protection now more than ever. We have worked closely with other organisations to build an elephant hospital in Sumatra to support this important species. We love Sumatran elephants with all our hearts and can’t wait to share them with you. We’re so proud to be continuing Steve’s legacy and his mission to protect elephants forever. 💚🐘

videos.title: 500k! Bindi & Chandler Thank YOU!
videos.description:
We've hit an incredible milestone - 500,000 subscribers on our YouTube channel! Join the Irwin family and Australia Zoo in this heartfelt thank you video.

From heartwarming rescues to unforgettable wildlife encounters, this video highlights our incredible journey together. Your support has made a significant impact on our mission of wildlife conservation and education.

Thank you for subscribing, liking, commenting, and sharing our videos. Your enthusiasm inspires us every day. Together, we're spreading love and awareness for our planet and its incredible creatures.

Join us as we celebrate our shared passion for wildlife. We're honored to have you in our community and can't wait to share more adventures with you.

videos.title: Morning kangaroo feed with Bindi & Chandler | Australia Zoo Life

videos.title: Robert’s insight into the complex world of croc research | Wildlife Warriors Missions
videos.description:
Our annual crocodile research trip has provided us with ground breaking discoveries into the world of the saltwater crocodile. It’s thanks to years of incredible work and dedication that we have successfully established a system for tracking these reptiles. But, how is it done? Robert takes us to the Wenlock river to explain one important step in the process, collecting data from acoustic hydrophones.

About Wildlife Warriors -

We are Wildlife Warriors. We fight for an extremely important cause – to protect our wildlife and wild places! Join us on our missions as we follow in the footsteps of the original Wildlife Warrior, Steve Irwin, and continue the work that he was so passionate about.

videos.title: We reflect on the incredible year that was, 2023!
videos.description:
How can you possibly fit all the amazing things that happened in 2023 into one video?!

Just to name a few highlights, this year we opened our Cheetah Grasslands habitat, provided a safe haven for and successfully hatched Elseya Irwini turtles, continued raising much needed funds for wildlife and wild places through Wildlife Warriors and learnt more about Australia’s incredible apex predator on our annual research trip to the Steve Irwin Wildlife Reserve.

We want to thank all of you for coming along for the journey. It’s thanks to your support that we are able to continue our conservation mission and keep Steve’s legacy alive. We can’t wait to share more with you in 2024!

About Wildlife Warriors -

We are Wildlife Warriors. We fight for an extremely important cause – to protect our wildlife and wild places! Join us on our missions as we follow in the footsteps of the original Wildlife Warrior, Steve Irwin, and continue the work that he was so passionate about.
From tigers in Sumatra and cheetahs in Africa, to saltwater crocodiles and koalas in Australia. The ultimate mission is to save one, save the species.

About Wildlife Warriors -

We are Wildlife Warriors. We fight for an extremely important cause – to protect our wildlife and wild places! Join us on our missions as we follow in the footsteps of the original Wildlife Warrior, Steve Irwin, and continue the work that he was so passionate about.
From tigers in Sumatra and cheetahs in Africa, to saltwater crocodiles and koalas in Australia. The ultimate mission is to save one, save the species.

Robert, Chandler & Grace visit the Australia Zoo Wildlife Hospital to check out some aquatic patients, starting with a truly amazing sea bird called a petrel.

About Wildlife Warriors -

We are Wildlife Warriors. We fight for an extremely important cause – to protect our wildlife and wild places! Join us on our missions as we follow in the footsteps of the original Wildlife Warrior, Steve Irwin, and continue the work that he was so passionate about.
From tigers in Sumatra and cheetahs in Africa, to saltwater crocodiles and koalas in Australia. The ultimate mission is to save one, save the species.

videos.title: Nostalgic Crocodile Action with Robert | Australia Zoo Life
videos.description:
As we unveil our newly renovated Crocoseum, let’s take a journey through time with Robert as he shows us the triple ponds! Our guests enjoyed daily feeds in these ponds while the Crocoseum underwent an exciting refurbishmen. These crocodile habitats were brought to life by Steve himself and stand strong to this day. Stick around for a heartwarming story from Terri as she shares a snippet of the moment her and Steve met for the first time.
#crocodile #action #wildlife

From tigers in Sumatra and cheetahs in Africa, to saltwater crocodiles and koalas in Australia. The ultimate mission is to save one, save the species.

videos.description:
Featuring exclusive Irwin family photos and animal fun facts.On your tour, learn about these amazing animals and their habitats. 

Observe how they live and grow and all the ways we can protect them. Get inspired to take part in nurturing your own environment and all that inhabit it. 

Most importantly, discover the Wildlife Warrior within!

From the daughter of Steve Irwin, The Crocodile Hunter, comes an illustrated picture book urging readers to walk on the wild side and uncover their inner conservationists.

videos.title: Rescue Diaries | An emotional reunion
videos.description:
We are Wildlife Warriors. We fight for an extremely important cause – to protect our wildlife and wild places! Join us on our missions as we follow in the footsteps of the original Wildlife Warrior, Steve Irwin, and continue the work that he was so passionate about.
From tigers in Sumatra and cheetahs in Africa, to saltwater crocodiles and koalas in Australia. The ultimate mission is to save one, save the species.

#swan # cute #wildlife #rescue
